	<div id='layer_slider_1'  class='avia-layerslider main_color avia-shadow  avia-builder-el-0  el_before_av_one_fourth  avia-builder-el-first  container_wrap fullsize'  style='height: 351px; max-width: 1150px; margin: 0 auto;'  ><link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Cabin:100,100i,200,200i,300,300i,400,400i,500,500i,600,600i,700,700i,800,800i,900,900i" rel="stylesheet"><div id="layerslider_5_1vqsua9w0nwdi" class="ls-wp-container fitvidsignore" style="width:1150px;height:350px;max-width:1150px;margin:0 auto;margin-bottom: 0px;"><div class="ls-slide" data-ls="duration:4000;transition2d:5;kenburnsscale:1.2;"><img width="1150" height="350" src="https://www.capetowndiamondmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/book-a-complimentary-diamond-tour.gif" class="ls-bg" alt="book a complimentary diamond tour" decoding="async" /><h2 style="top:60px;left:110px;text-align:initial;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;mix-blend-mode:normal;font-size:40px;line-height:50px;color:#ffff;width:320px;font-family:'Cabin', sans-serif;;white-space:normal;" class="ls-l ls-text-layer" data-ls="showinfo:1;position:relative;">WELCOME TO THE WORLD OF DIAMONDS</h2><a href="/contact/booking-form/" target="_self" class="ls-link ls-link-on-top" rel="noopener"></a></div><div class="ls-slide" data-ls="duration:4000;transition2d:5;kenburnsscale:1.2;"><img width="1150" height="350" src="https://www.capetowndiamondmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cullinan-rough-diamond.gif" class="ls-bg" alt="the cullinan rough diamond" decoding="async" /><h2 style="text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:300;width:320px;font-family:'Cabin', sans-serif;;font-size:40px;line-height:50px;color:#ffffff;top:60px;left:110px;white-space:normal;" class="ls-l ls-text-layer" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;">The Cullinan Diamond 3,106ct</h2><p style="width:320px;font-size:14px;line-height:18px;color:#B3B3B3;top:230px;left:110px;white-space:normal;" class="ls-l ls-text-layer" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;">The Cullinan, discovered in South Africa in 1905, is the
largest gem quality diamond ever found.</p><a style="" class="ls-l" href="/about-diamonds/famous-diamonds/" target="_self" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;" rel="noopener"><p style="width:320px;color:#A7805A;top:285px;left:110px;" class="ls-text-layer">Discover more famous diamonds</p></a><a href="/about-diamonds/famous-diamonds/" target="_self" class="ls-link ls-link-on-top" rel="noopener"></a></div><div class="ls-slide" data-ls="duration:4000;transition2d:5;"><img width="1150" height="350" src="https://www.capetowndiamondmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cape-town-diamond-museum-learn-about-the-4csp-of-diamond-grading.gif" class="ls-bg" alt="learn about the 4Cs of diamond grading" decoding="async" /><h2 style="text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:300;width:320px;font-family:'Cabin', sans-serif;;font-size:40px;line-height:50px;color:#ffffff;top:60px;left:110px;white-space:normal;" class="ls-l ls-text-layer" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;">The 4Cs of Diamond Grading</h2><p style="width:320px;font-size:14px;line-height:18px;color:#B3B3B3;top:230px;left:110px;white-space:normal;" class="ls-l ls-text-layer" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;">Diamonds are graded using a universal system
based on their colour, clarity, cut and carat-weight...</p><a style="" class="ls-l" href="/about-diamonds/4-cs/" target="_self" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;" rel="noopener"><p style="width:320px;color:#A7805A;top:300px;left:110px;" class="ls-text-layer">Learn more about diamond grading</p></a><a href="/about-diamonds/4-cs/" target="_self" class="ls-link ls-link-on-top" rel="noopener"></a></div><div class="ls-slide" data-ls="duration:4000;transition2d:5;"><img width="1150" height="350" src="https://www.capetowndiamondmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cape-town-diamond-museum-diamonds-through-the-ages.gif" class="ls-bg" alt="Diamonds through the ages" decoding="async" /><h2 style="text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:300;width:320px;font-family:'Cabin', sans-serif;;font-size:40px;line-height:50px;color:#ffffff;top:60px;left:110px;white-space:normal;" class="ls-l ls-text-layer" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;">Diamonds through the ages</h2><p style="width:320px;font-size:14px;line-height:18px;color:#B3B3B3;top:230px;left:110px;white-space:normal;" class="ls-l ls-text-layer" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;">The history of diamonds stems over billions of years and the
tale is one of mystical power, beauty, wealth...</p><a style="" class="ls-l" href="/about-diamonds/diamonds-through-the-ages/" target="_self" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;" rel="noopener"><p style="width:320px;color:#A7805A;top:300px;left:110px;" class="ls-text-layer">Learn more about the history of diamonds</p></a><a href="/about-diamonds/diamonds-through-the-ages/" target="_self" class="ls-link ls-link-on-top" rel="noopener"></a></div><div class="ls-slide" data-ls="duration:4000;transition2d:5;"><img width="1150" height="350" src="https://www.capetowndiamondmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/diamond-shapes-and-cuts.gif" class="ls-bg" alt="learn about diamond shapes and cuts" decoding="async" /><h2 style="text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:300;width:300px;font-family:'Cabin', sans-serif;;font-size:40px;line-height:50px;color:#ffffff;top:60px;left:110px;white-space:normal;" class="ls-l ls-text-layer" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;">Discover Diamond Shapes</h2><p style="width:250px;font-size:14px;line-height:18px;color:#B3B3B3;top:230px;left:110px;white-space:normal;" class="ls-l ls-text-layer" data-ls="offsetxin:80;offsetxout:-80;durationout:400;parallaxlevel:0;">Unique characteristics determine the quality
